			"body": "<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: summarize by coderabbit.ai -->\nNo actionable comments were generated in the recent review. 🎉\n\n<details>\n<summary>ℹ️ Recent review info</summary>\n\n<details>\n<summary>⚙️ Run configuration</summary>\n\n**Configuration used**: Path: .coderabbit.yaml\n\n**Review profile**: CHILL\n\n**Plan**: Pro\n\n**Run ID**: `898d9783-16b3-4f3b-94ee-6c6b20f78822`\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary>📥 Commits</summary>\n\nReviewing files that changed from the base of the PR and between 68ed2a868e97e43ebeb85ce5bb21e55b03d51c40 and 7578916060f1e5f5104f0ba1c892bd0bc3026029.\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary>⛔ Files ignored due to path filters (1)</summary>\n\n* `yarn.lock` is excluded by `!**/yarn.lock`, `!**/*.lock`\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary>📒 Files selected for processing (1)</summary>\n\n* `packages/app-desktop/gui/MasterPasswordDialog/Dialog.tsx`\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary>🚧 Files skipped from review as they are similar to previous changes (1)</summary>\n\n* packages/app-desktop/gui/MasterPasswordDialog/Dialog.tsx\n\n</details>\n\n</details>\n\n---\n\n\n<!-- walkthrough_start -->\n\n<details>\n<summary>📝 Walkthrough</summary>\n\n## Walkthrough\n\nAdds a zxcvbn-based password strength utility and tests, updates lib dependencies, and integrates a real-time password strength indicator into the Master Password dialog UI.\n\n## Changes\n\n|Cohort / File(s)|Summary|\n|---|---|\n|**Password strength library & tests** <br> `packages/lib/services/e2ee/passwordStrength.ts`, `packages/lib/services/e2ee/passwordStrength.test.ts`|New exports: `PasswordStrengthResult` interface, `passwordStrengthLabels`, and `getPasswordStrength(password)` which normalises zxcvbn output; unit tests for empty, weak, moderate and strong passwords.|\n|**Dependencies** <br> `packages/lib/package.json`|Added runtime dependency `zxcvbn` (`4.4.2`) and dev dependency `@types/zxcvbn`.|\n|**Master Password dialog UI** <br> `packages/app-desktop/gui/MasterPasswordDialog/Dialog.tsx`|Integrates a visual strength indicator beneath the first password input via a new `renderStrengthIndicator()` flow that calls `getPasswordStrength`; includes dynamic colour, label, percentage and optional feedback. No public API changes.|\n\n## Sequence Diagram(s)\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant User\n    participant UI as MasterPasswordDialog\n    participant Lib as getPasswordStrength()\n    participant Zxcvbn as zxcvbn\n\n    User->>UI: Type password\n    UI->>Lib: getPasswordStrength(password)\n    Lib->>Zxcvbn: evaluate password\n    Zxcvbn-->>Lib: score + feedback\n    Lib-->>UI: { score, feedback, label }\n    UI-->>User: render strength bar, label and feedback\n```\n\n## Possibly related issues\n\n- laurent22/joplin#14760 — Both implement a real-time password strength indicator for the Master Password UI; aligns with this PR's feature and target component.\n\n## Possibly related PRs\n\n- laurent22/joplin#14752 — Modifies the same MasterPasswordDialog/Dialog.tsx UI and localises hardcoded strings used in the password form.\n- laurent22/joplin#14566 — Adds inline password feedback in MasterPasswordDialog/Dialog.tsx (similar UI location and behaviour).\n\n## Suggested reviewers\n\n- mrjo118\n\n</details>\n\n<!-- walkthrough_end -->\n\n\n<!-- pre_merge_checks_walkthrough_start -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- pre_merge_checks_override_start -->\n> [!IMPORTANT]\n> ## Pre-merge checks failed\n> \n> Please resolve all errors before merging. Addressing warnings is optional.\n<!-- pre_merge_checks_override_end -->\n\n### ❌ Failed checks (1 error)\n\n|               Check name              | Status  | Explanation                                                                                                                                                       | Resolution                                                                                                                                                              